parameters.name: LR_OFFSET_TIME0
parameters.description:
The delta time offset from MET for the first low-rate
   data sample in the LRHK packet (in steps of 50 milliseconds). Provides 50
   msec resolution.

parameters.name: MIN_INTERVAL
parameters.description:
The minimum derived sampling interval in seconds.
   Determined by taking the minimum time difference between successive
   timestamps in the LRHK packet.

parameters.name: MAX_INTERVAL
parameters.description:
The maximum derived sampling interval in seconds.
   Determined by taking the maximum time difference between successive
   timestamps in the LRHK packet.

parameters.name: NUM_LR_SAMPLES
parameters.description: Number of low-rate sample data in the LRHK packet.

parameters.name: MAG_DC_DC_CURR
parameters.description:
The derived MAG DC/DC current; used following formula:
   if the DN (telemetry value) is less than 128:
      MAG_DC_DC_CURR = DN/64
   else
      MAG_DC_DC_CURR = (DN-256)/64
   The resulting value is in units of amperes.

parameters.name: PROBE_TEMP
parameters.description:
The derived MAG probe temperature:
     PROBE_TEMP = 0.0123*(DN**2) - 0.7316*DN - 144.85. Value is in units of
     degrees Celsius.

parameters.name: MAG_ELEC_TEMP
parameters.description:
The derived MAG electronics temperature:
     MAG_ELEC_TEMP = (155*DN/127) - 55
    The value for this column is in units of degrees Celsius.
